Jeanette Chabalala, News24(News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; About 36 prisoners have sustained serious to minor injuries following a fire at Leeuwkop prison, Gauteng paramedics said on Friday. &nbsp;The incident happened on Friday at about 14:00, Netcare911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said in a statement.&nbsp;Mathe said reports from the scene indicate that two prisoners were in critical condition. She said paramedics were at the scene treating prisoners for smoke inhalation and burn wounds.Those who require further medical care will be transported to various hospitals in Johannesburg, she said.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.